dismissalText.commentary: Michael Hussey c Elliott b O'Brien 49 (65b 1x4 1x6 99m) SR: 75.38

dismissalComment.html: first ball of the Powerplay gets a wicket, Hussey has to go, he tried to chip a length ball over the infield, mid-off was on the edge of the circle, and it's a simple catch for him, Hussey's innings ends at 49

dismissalText.commentary: Brad Haddin b Mills 31 (54b 1x4 1x6 57m) SR: 57.4

dismissalComment.html: dragged on! Haddin advances to a full one just outside off stump and goes for a drive but can only succeed in inside-edging back onto his stumps and Mills celebrates

Marsh is gone, he chips a length delivery to the two-metre tall Peter Fulton at short cover, Fulton had to jump to hold on to that chance, good reflexes from Fulton, Marsh had looked in good touch during his short stay

Warner's gone, similar dismissal to Marsh's, shortish ball, gave Warner room to free his arms, he cuts it but gives Fulton at short cover a much simple catch, Fulton didn't have to move and that came to him at a nice catchable height, around his chest
dragged on! Haddin advances to a full one just outside off stump and goes for a drive but can only succeed in inside-edging back onto his stumps and Mills celebrates
and that's the end of the innings, Johnson goes for a big swipe over midwicket, doesn't make contact with the ball, which homes in on the leg bail, Australia fold for 181

dismissalText.commentary: Neil Broom b Clarke 29 (50b 2x4 0x6 52m) SR: 58

dismissalComment.html: Australia claw back, now there's a bit of controversy here, Clarke gets it to skid through on a good length, Broom makes a lot of room to cut but he's beaten for pace, the ball appears to clip the top of the off bail but replays indicate that Haddin had his gloves in front of the stumps before the ball could make contact. Did the ball actually hit the stumps? Did Haddin whip off the bails by mistake? Very inconclusive but no wonder Broom looked perplexed as he walked back

commentPreTextItems.html: The field comes in, Patel gets rid of his helmet, and his gloves. He wants to feel as light as possible.

commentTextItems.html: he's done it! Vettori's hit the winning run! Bracken bowls a full ball outside off stump, he was looking for the yorker no doubt.Vettori loves width outside off, he loves the cut, and he places the ball through backward point and yells in triumph

commentPostTextItems.html: 9.50 pm: What a superb low-scoring thriller at the WACA. New Zealand pip Australia by two wickets off the last ball. They'll be mighty thrilled with the effort but it should have never got this close.

Kyle Mills is the Player of the Match for taking four wickets and then scoring 26 runs just when the chase got really tense. The next game is on Friday at the MCG, do join us for that. Thank you for your emails, on behalf of today's commentary team (Jamie, Sid R, and Kanishkaa) this is George Binoy signing off. Good night!

commentTextItems.html: just opens the face of the bat and steers it to short third man, New Zealand can't lose now, the scores are level
fires in the yorker and he gets underneath a low full toss and works it away to deep square leg

commentPostTextItems.html: There's never been a tie between these two sides in ODIs

commentTextItems.html: gets forward and steers it down to backward point and the batsmen are struggling, the fielder has a shy at the bowler';s stumps and Patel is nowhere in the scene

dismissalText.commentary: Tim Southee b Bracken 3 (6b 0x4 0x6 11m) SR: 50

commentPreTextItems.html: 4 to get off 5, Southee on strike, the keeper is standing behind

commentTextItems.html: timber! Bracken bowls that deadly off cutter and Southee fails to pick the slower ball, he exposes his leg stump and tries to heave it away over square leg as the ball thuds on to his middle stump
fires that on the blockhole and he pushes it firmly through the line to long-on
backs away and Tait bangs it in short, he adjusts his stroke and slices it down to third man

commentTextItems.html: fires in the yorker outside off and he gets forward and digs it out wide of point
he bangs in the bouncer from round the wicket and Vettoru ducks under it hoping it will be called a no ball, Bucknor at square leg signals one for the over
comes round the wicket, Vettori backs away too far and he fails to make any contact
he makes room and exposes all three stumps, he gets an inside edge past the stumps and Haddin does really well to save it, they steal a run
bangs it in short, he tries to hook but misses
beaten outside the off stump, they steal a bye

dismissalText.commentary: Ricky Ponting run out (Broom/McCullum) 5 (13b 0x4 0x6 18m) SR: 38.46

dismissalComment.html: Ponting's run out! he turns a full ball towards square leg , Neil Broom is the fielder, he's on to the ball in a flash, the throw is fantastic as well, powerful and accurate, McCullum whips the bails off and Ponting is a couple of feet short of the crease

dismissalText.commentary: Michael Clarke run out (Guptill/McCullum) 12 (27b 1x4 0x6 35m) SR: 44.44

dismissalComment.html: Another run-out! Clarke's gone, he square drives it past the diving backward point, Guptill does the fielding at the boundary, the throw is wonderful again, one-bounce and on top of the stumps, Clarke's inches short of making it as McCullum takes off the bails

dismissalComment.html: well held, Mitchell! A very scratchy innings comes to an end courtesy a superb reflex catch from Johnson, who pitches it up on off stump and then sticks out his left hand as he tumbles down in his followthrough, plucking the checked off-drive back in the air rather excellently

dismissalText.commentary: Ross Taylor c Clarke b Bracken 64 (97b 6x4 1x6 175m) SR: 65.97

dismissalComment.html: a fabulous catch by Clarke and we have a twist in the tale here, Bracken pitches it up outside off, he walks across his stumps, reaches forward and slices it on the up to backward point, Clarke flings himself to his left and cups it with both hands

dismissalText.commentary: Neil Broom b Clarke 29 (50b 2x4 0x6 52m) SR: 58

dismissalComment.html: Australia claw back, now there's a bit of controversy here, Clarke gets it to skid through on a good length, Broom makes a lot of room to cut but he's beaten for pace, the ball appears to clip the top of the off bail but replays indicate that Haddin had his gloves in front of the stumps before the ball could make contact. Did the ball actually hit the stumps? Did Haddin whip off the bails by mistake? Very inconclusive but no wonder Broom looked perplexed as he walked back

dismissalText.commentary: Kyle Mills b Tait 26 (35b 3x4 0x6 55m) SR: 74.28

dismissalComment.html: he gets a little too cheeky and loses his wicket, he makes way too much room and exposes all three stumps, Tait fires in a fast yorker and hits the middle stump, now will this wicket change things a bit?

dismissalText.commentary: Daniel Vettori not out 7 (9b 0x4 0x6 26m) SR: 77.77
